President Donald J. Trump spoke with Chancellor Angela Merkel of Germany, President Emmanuel Macron of France, Prime Minister Justin Trudeau of Canada, and Prime Minister Theresa May of the United Kingdom to personally explain his decision to withdraw the United States from the Paris Climate Accord. He thanked the leaders for their discussions on this issue and reassured them that America remains committed to the Transatlantic alliance and protecting the environment. Trump highlighted America's efforts in reducing emissions and developing clean energy technology, stating that the United States will be the cleanest and most environmentally friendly country under his administration. The leaders agreed to continue dialogue and strengthen cooperation on environmental and other issues.